OL,4,BJim Bentley: Morecambe manager resigns
OL,5,Band becomes AFC Fylde boss
OL,6, Jim Bentley has resigned as manager of
OL,7, League Two's bottom club Morecambe to
OL,8, take charge of National League side AFC
OL,9, Fylde on a two-and-a-half-year deal.
OL,11,FThe 43-year-old was the longest-serving
OL,12,Fmanager in England's top four divisions
OL,13,Fbefore his resignation on Monday.
OL,15,FBentley had been Shrimps boss since May
OL,16,F2011, having previously spent nine
OL,17,Fyears with the club as a player.
OL,19,FThe former centre-back has dropped a
OL,20,Fdivision to join Fylde, who sacked Dave
OL,21,FChallinor on 12 October.
